<p>50<br/>a pleasant evening of it. The nights are very sharp now, all available clothes go on the bed before turning in. We are to be issued with an extra blanket to-day I believe tr&egrave;s bon.</p>
<p>The Colonel returns to-day from leave in London. Have had Major Charlton Commanding in his absence.</p>
<p>25-9/16 Monday.<br/>Went to Church last night first time for a long while. The speaker was great could have listened all night. Had some old hymns which took me back home.</p>
<p>The weather has been beautiful lately the days are quite warm.</p>
<p>27-9-6.<br/>Reported to-day that Thiepval has been taken. The Colonel brought the news from D.H.Q.</p>
